# Phase 6 — Semantic Search & Scraper Proxies

This phase introduces **Semantic Search** and **Similar Course Recommendations** using PostgreSQL's `pgvector` extension and local embeddings, alongside a **Proxy Configuration Manager** to protect scrapers and the expiry validator from Cloudflare blocks and rate limits.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Image Upgrade**: To support vector databases, we must upgrade the PostgreSQL image in `docker-compose.yml` from `postgres:16-alpine` to `pgvector/pgvector:16-pgvector`. If you have existing local volumes, docker will restart with the new image seamlessly, but we will run `CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;` in a Prisma migration to initialize pgvector.
> **Please confirm if you have any constraints on changing the database container image.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Local Embedding Generation**: We will use `@huggingface/transformers` in the NestJS backend to run the lightweight **`Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2`** model (~90MB model file) locally on CPU. This converts course metadata and user search queries into 384-dimensional vectors. Embedding generation will run asynchronously in a background queue so it does not block course storage.
> **Please confirm if you prefer this local approach or if you'd like to support optional OpenAI/Gemini API configurations in `.env`.**

